I haven't checked if this also occurs on other platforms as well.  
The same thing also happens with typing new characters and not only with selecting text.

## Steps to Reproduce

1. Execute `flutter run -d chrome` on the code sample
2. Type something into the text field.
3. Press ctrl+a to see that all the text in the field gets selected.
4. Click into the text field to de-select the text
5. Hit enter to submit the field.
6. Press ctrl+a again. 

**Expected results:** The text should be selected again.

**Actual results:** The text doesn't get selected, but the text field is still focused so it should just select the text. When clicking into the text field again and then pressing ctrl+a again, it works just fine.

<details>
<summary>Code sample</summary>

```dart
import 'package:flutter/material.dart';

void main() {
  runApp(const MyApp());
}

class MyApp extends StatelessWidget {
  const MyApp({Key? key}) : super(key: key);

  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) => MaterialApp(
        home: HomePage(),
      );
}

class HomePage extends StatelessWidget {
  HomePage({Key? key}) : super(key: key);

  final _focusNode = FocusNode();

  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return Scaffold(
      body: TextField(
        focusNode: _focusNode,
        onSubmitted: (_) {
          _focusNode.requestFocus();
        },
      ),
    );
  }
}
```

</details>

