For my case, I found the root cause was the script which intend to run Flutter App in the **index.html** file. I update the script as below and everything worked fine:

```
<script>
    window.addEventListener('load', function(ev) {
        var loading = document.querySelector('#loading');
        loading.textContent = "Loading entrypoint...";
        _flutter.loader.loadEntrypoint({
          serviceWorker: {
            serviceWorkerVersion: serviceWorkerVersion,
          },
          onEntrypointLoaded: async function(engineInitializer) {
            loading.textContent = "Initializing engine...";
            let appRunner = await engineInitializer.initializeEngine();

            loading.textContent = "Running app...";
            await appRunner.runApp();
          }
        });
      });
  </script>
```

I ran into this bug in `reactive_forms` while implementing a growing `ReactiveFormArray`. In my case the focused `TextField` widget would rebuild as new fields were added. After the rebuild `TextField` regains focus automatically even though the cursor inside the `TextField` is missing and no text input is possible even though `hasFocus = true`.

The workaround in my case was to first unfocus the `TextField` before requesting focus with a small time delay. 

```
_focusNode.unfocus();

Future.delayed(const Duration(milliseconds: 5), () {
 _focusNode.requestFocus();
  
});
```

